{
  "texts": [
    "In our dataset, the longest MARLIN feature length was 56, the shortest was 2, and the average length was 23.10 ± 14.45.",
    "We then employed a deep sequential model, TCN, as the temporal feature extractor in F φ.",
    "TCN has been previously used for predicting learning engagement using the facial emotion recognition model's middle layer features from videos (Abedi and Khan, 2021).",
    "We use the penultimate layer output of the TCN module as the high-level facial video features.",
    "We pass these features through a linear layer with a batch normalization layer and hyperbolic tangent function to obtain a scalar representation."
  ]
}